data.title: THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING; PEOPLE MAGAZINE HAS DEAL WITH WALT DISNEY
data.meta_description: LEAD: People magazine, one of the Time Inc. stable, has made a two-pronged money-making deal with the Walt Disney Company pegged to Mickey Mouse's 60th birthday.
data.text:
LEAD: People magazine, one of the Time Inc. stable, has made a two-pronged money-making deal with the Walt Disney Company pegged to Mickey Mouse's 60th birthday.

People magazine, one of the Time Inc. stable, has made a two-pronged money-making deal with the Walt Disney Company pegged to Mickey Mouse's 60th birthday.

Part I is a 64-page commemorative magazine under the Disney logotype due out Aug. 1, with a cover price of $2.50. Part II will be 32-page inserts that will run in November in all Time Inc. magazines except Sports Illustrated.

While the same insert will run in both People and Southern Living, the other three for Time, Fortune and Life will be tailored for each magazine.
